  "title": "Senior Staff Nurse (Welfare Home) - North-East",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist the Superintendent in managing the Welfare Home </li>\n  <li>Plan, manage, and oversee the safe and efficient delivery of quality healthcare services to residents</li>\n  <li>Ensure all healthcare services comply with relevant legislation, SOPs, service standards, guidelines, and official directives</li>\n  <li>Provide preventive and curative medical care to residents under the supervision and direction of medical doctor(s)</li>\n  <li>Support continuous improvement of healthcare practices within the Home</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Degree/ Advanced Diploma in Nursing</strong></li>\n  <li>Registered with the Singapore Nursing Board</li>\n  <li><strong>Minimum 3 to 5 years of experience in a supervisory, management, or leadership role</strong></li>\n  <li>Preferably with experience in aged care, social service, or therapy-integrated environments</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge in policy development, quality management, and staff supervision</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
